# Sunday School Study Companion Cursor Rules

- Read `AGENTS.md` and `docs/context-map.md` before editing. Use root `ARCHITECTURE.md` for current technical details.
- Stack: React + TypeScript + Vite in `src/`, TypeScript Azure Functions in `api/`, shared Zod contracts in `shared/`, Cosmos DB through `/api`, static fallback JSON in `public/data/`.
- Frontend code calls `/api` only. Do not call the Exam API from browser code.
- Do not commit or print real secrets, JWTs, deployment tokens, Cosmos keys, passwords, or app setting values.
- Public/student payloads must not expose user IDs, names, emails, phone numbers, school IDs, private notes, raw pending patches, or audit records.
- Before implementing a new UI feature, show the user an ASCII mock and wait for confirmation.
- Update `ARCHITECTURE.md` when structure, routes, modules, env vars, deployment, infrastructure, or runtime flow changes.
- Keep `public/data/` on the current shared contract; it is fallback/manual reference only.
- Production mutations, deploys, DNS updates, and Cosmos seed/migrate/prune require explicit user confirmation immediately before execution.
- Validation: `python3 scripts/check-ai-context.py`, `npm run typecheck`, `npm run build`, `npm run --prefix api build`, and `npm run --prefix api cosmos:inspect` as relevant.
- There is currently no lint script or dedicated test runner; do not claim lint/tests ran unless added and executed.
